CloudFrontAPI provides an interface to enable mocking the cloudfront.CloudFront service client's API operation, paginators, and waiters. This make unit testing your code that calls out to the SDK's service client's calls easier.

The best way to use this interface is so the SDK's service client's calls can be stubbed out for unit testing your code with the SDK without needing to inject custom request handlers into the SDK's request pipeline. 

// myFunc uses an SDK service client to make a request to
// Amazon CloudFront.
func myFunc(svc cloudfrontiface.CloudFrontAPI) bool {
    // Make svc.AssociateAlias request
}

func main() {
    sess := session.New()
    svc := cloudfront.New(sess)

    myFunc(svc)
}

In your _test.go file: 

// Define a mock struct to be used in your unit tests of myFunc.
type mockCloudFrontClient struct {
    cloudfrontiface.CloudFrontAPI
}
func (m *mockCloudFrontClient) AssociateAlias(input *cloudfront.AssociateAliasInput) (*cloudfront.AssociateAliasOutput, error) {
    // mock response/functionality
}

func TestMyFunc(t *testing.T) {
    // Setup Test
    mockSvc := &mockCloudFrontClient{}

    myfunc(mockSvc)

    // Verify myFunc's functionality
}
